@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/v1
@token = your_jwt_token_here

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#  BM2MALL API TEST FILE
#  Base URL : http://localhost:3000/v1
#
#  SETUP STEPS:
#  Step 1 → Run "1.2 Send OTP"    (use your registered mobile)
#  Step 2 → Run "1.3 Verify OTP"  (OTP = 111111 in dev mode)
#  Step 3 → Copy data.token from response → paste into @token above
#  Step 4 → Now all protected routes will work
#
#  CART RULE (IMPORTANT!):
#  When adding to cart, productId ≠ product list `id`
#  From GET /products/15 response:
#    data.id        = 15    ← use this in product URLs
#    data.productId = 5014  ← use THIS in cart requests
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### ════════════════════════════════════════════
### 1. AUTHENTICATION
### ════════════════════════════════════════════


### 1.1 Register
# ✏️  EDIT: Change fullName, mobile, email to your values
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Test User",
  "mobile": "9876543210",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

# ✅ EXPECTED RESPONSE (201 Created):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "msg": "signup successful",
#   "data": null
# }
#
# ❌ ERROR (400) — mobile already registered:
# { "success": false, "msg": "mobile number already registered." }

###

### 1.2 Send OTP
# ✏️  EDIT: Change mobile to your registered number
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mobile": "9876543210"
}

# ✅ EXPECTED RESPONSE (200 OK):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "msg": "otp sent successfully",
#   "data": null
# }
#
# ❌ ERROR (404) — number not registered:
# { "success": false, "msg": "mobile number not registered. please signup first." }
#
# ❌ ERROR (429) — OTP requested too soon:
# { "success": false, "msg": "please wait 60 seconds before requesting a new otp." }

###

### 1.3 Verify OTP  ← After running, copy data.token into @token above
# ✏️  EDIT: Change mobile to your number (OTP stays 111111 in dev)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mobile": "9876543210",
  "otp": "111111"
}

# ✅ EXPECTED RESPONSE (200 OK):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "msg": "otp verified successfully",
#   "data": {
#     "user": {
#       "id": 15,
#       "mobile": "9876543210",
#       "name": "Test User"
#     }
#   }
# }
#
# ❌ ERROR (400) — wrong otp:
# { "success": false, "msg": "invalid otp" }
#
# ❌ ERROR (400) — otp expired:
# { "success": false, "msg": "otp has expired" }

###

### 1.4 Logout
# ✏️  ENSURE: @token is set from Verify OTP response
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ✅ EXPECTED RESPONSE (200 OK):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "msg": "logged out successfully",
#   "data": null
# }
#
# ❌ ERROR (401) — invalid/missing token:
# { "success": false, "code": "ERR_AUTH", "msg": "unauthorized" }

###

# 1.5 Refresh Token
# ✏️ ENSURE: @token is set from Verify OTP response
# ⚠️ Optional: You can also send refreshToken in body, otherwise cookie will be used
### ════════════════════════════════════════════

POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json
 
# ✅ EXPECTED RESPONSE (200 OK):
# {
# "success": true,
# "msg": "token refreshed successfully",
# "data": {
# "user": {
# "id": 15,
# "mobile": "9876543210",
# "name": "Test User"
# }
# }
# }
//❌ ERROR (401) — missing/invalid/expired refresh token:
// { "success": false, "msg": "Invalid or expired refresh token" }  only add this endpoint


### ════════════════════════════════════════════
### 2. PROFILE
### ════════════════════════════════════════════


### 2.1 Get My Profile
# ✏️  ENSURE: @token is set
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ✅ EXPECTED RESPONSE (200 OK):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "id": 15,
#     "fullName": "Test User",
#     "mobile": "9876543210",
#     "email": "test@example.com",
#     "profileImage": null
#   }
# }



### 2.2 Update Profile
# ✏️  EDIT: Change fullName and email values as needed
# ✏️  ENSURE: @token is set
# Note: profileImage file upload only works via Postman/Thunder Client
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/profile/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary7MA4YWx

------FormBoundary7MA4YWx
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="fullName"

John Updated
------FormBoundary7MA4YWx
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

john.updated@example.com
------FormBoundary7MA4YWx--

# ✅ EXPECTED RESPONSE (200 OK):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "id": 15,
#     "fullName": "John Updated",
#     "email": "john.updated@example.com",
#     ...
#   }
# }

### 2.3 Upload Profile Photo
# ✏️  ENSURE: @token is set
# Note: File upload only works via Postman/Thunder Client / VS Code Rest Client
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/profile/upload-photo
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundaryPhoto

------FormBoundaryPhoto
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="profileImage"; filename="avatar.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./avatar.jpg
------FormBoundaryPhoto--

# ✅ EXPECTED RESPONSE (200 OK):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "msg": "Profile photo uploaded successfully",
#   "data": { "url": "https://res.cloudinary.com/..." }
# }


